RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 62. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $3,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOLD MISTRESS was sent to establish the early advantage, was well handled through decent fractions to the quarter marker, drew off into the stretch and was kept to task to the wire to prevail as much the best. RIVIERA SUNRISE chased from the inside, was not able to impact the winner in the drive, was able to close a bit of ground in the final furlong and bested the rest. JERSEY BIRD chased from midflight while outside of rivals, was steered three wide into the stretch, could not keep pace into the final furlong, was outfinished for second and held for third at the wire. ENGEE OMBEE lacked early speed, was coaxed along four wide into the stretch, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and missed for third. MANY MARKETS was prominent in the early stages, stalked the decent pace along the turn, could not match strides heading to mid-stretch and gave way in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Engee Ombee
ENTRY.OWNER: Sandlot Racing Stables and Lininger Paul
ENTRY.COMMENT: lacked speed,4wide into stretch,needed more late,missed 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Riviera Sunrise
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside,mild late bid,no match,2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Jersey Bird
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased outside,3wide into stretch,outfinished for 2nd,held for 3d

ENTRY.NAME: Bold Mistress
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,well handled,drew off stretch,kept to task,held sway

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 91. Claiming Purse 16000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LESSONS OF AUTISM stalked the decent early pace while between rivals, slipped to the rail along the turn and was well placed at the quarter marker, was roused four wide into the stretch, closed well inside of the furlong pole, overtook WOUND UP at the sixteenth-marker and drew away in the final stages. WOUND UP was asked for early speed and dictated terms into the turn, was pressed to the quarter marker then shook free into upper stretch, was overtaken by LESSONS OF AUTISM at the sixteenth-marker and held for second at the finish. ZIPPY BABY raced close to the early pace while outside of rivals, pressed WOUND UP to the quarter marker, lost a bit of ground into the stretch, remained within striking distance to the sixteenth-marker, was outkicked in deep stretch and missed for second, while clear for third. HARBOR SKY bobbled at the start and was off slowly, chased from the rear along the turn and lacked a late response.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 3 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 27000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Non-starters For Claiming Price $16,000 Or Less In The Last Three Starts Preferred)(Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won An Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs. Unless Entered For A Clai ming Price).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DERRYGOOLIN broke alertly and assumed command at the start, set moderate fractions while prompted through the backstretch run, held a narrow lead to the quarter marker, shook free into upper stretch, dug in under firm urging inside of the furlong marker, felt late pressure from the oncoming runner-up and lasted for the win at the finish. BOLD DAUGHTER was unhurried while not far back in the early stages, tracked the moderate pace through the backstretch run, chased outside of runners along the far turn and came four wide into the stretch, made a steady advance inside of the furlong marker, rallied in deep stretch and missed for the win, while clear of the rest for second. MOMMA MOCCA was forwardly placed while outside of rivals into the first turn, prompted the moderate pace through the backstretch run, lost a bit of ground heading to the quarter marker, chased DERRYGOOLIN to mid-stretch, weakened in the final stages and was outfinished for second, while clear for third. BLUSHING BAY stalked the pace into the first turn then took back to settle through the backstretch run, swung widest into the stretch, raced in the five path in the drive and did not threaten in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Blushing Bay
ENTRY.OWNER: Padilla Andres and Flores De La Torre Teresa
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked early,took back,swung widest upper,no threat late

ENTRY.NAME: Bold Daughter
ENTRY.COMMENT: not far back,3-4wide 2nd turn,rallied stretch,just missed

ENTRY.NAME: Momma Mocca
ENTRY.OWNER: Gutierrez Matthew Hanna Mark A Hanna Maria and Martin Ralph

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 93. Waiver Claiming Purse 18000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since May 15 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races Fo r $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SATANTA tracked the decent pace from the inside, angled three wide nearing the top of the stretch, closed well inside of the furlong marker, overtook GREAT STORY nearing the sixteenth-pole and drew away in a drive in the final stages. GREAT STORY broke alertly and showed good early speed, dueled with ZHIVAGO to the turn, took a narrow lead along the bend while carving decent fractions, drew to a clear advantage into the stretch, could not hold off the winner inside of the sixteenth-marker and held well for second at the finish. PAPAPIFAS stalked the decent early pace, advanced outside of rivals on the turn, was coaxed along four wide into the stretch, was outfinished in the drive and held clearly for third. GRIT AND CURIOSITY chased the decent pace from the inside, gained ground into upper stretch, lacked the needed response in the final furlong and finished evenly. MOUNT PELLIAR broke awkwardly and was off slowly, chased outside of a rival through the turn and did not threaten in the stretch. ZHIVAGO pressed the solid early pace, kept close attendance to GREAT STORY to the quarter marker, could not keep pace in the stretch and tired in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Grit and Curiosity
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside,bid upper,needed more late,evenly stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Great Story
ENTRY.OWNER: Hunsucker Lester Paredes Jose and Trujillo Victor

ENTRY.NAME: Satanta
ENTRY.OWNER: MJ Ranch Alvarado Esmeralda Ramirez Luis and Ruiz Salvador
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside,angled 3wide,closed well stretch,drew away late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DADS DREAM broke alertly, took back and raced close to the decent early pace, stalked the leaders three wide approaching the quarter marker, was roused into upper stretch, took command at the furlong marker, drew to a clear lead inside of the furlong pole, drew off under moderate urging nearing the sixteenth-marker and was geared down in the final stages as much the best. MIRAGE CODE was bumped leaving the break and was off a step slowly, was hustled in the early stages and showed speed to take a narrow lead into the turn, set decent fractions while pressed to the quarter marker, was overtaken by the winner heading to the furlong pole, was no match for DADS DREAM in the final stages and bested the rest. DAD'S JUBILEE pressed the decent early pace, kept pressure on the MIRAGE CODE while between rivals into upper stretch, could not keep pace with the top pair into the drive and weakened late, while holding clearly for third. SPIDER PIG lacked early speed, saved ground to the top of the stretch and did not threaten. KLIMT A. P. broke in soon after the break and bumped MIRAGE CODE, chased the early pace while outside of rivals, was coaxed along three wide into the lane and did not factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Dad's Jubilee
ENTRY.OWNER: Moger Inc Nick of Time Thoroughbreds Estrada Aldo Kropp Gary Kropp Janet and Pim

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 12500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PERFORMATIVE broke alertly, took back off of the fast early pace and stalked outside of rivals into the turn, advanced four then three wide along the turn, took command in upper stretch, held a narrow lead to the furlong grounds, jumped a track in deep stretch and kept to task in the final stages to prevail. COBRE chased the solid early pace while widest into the turn, improved position four wide nearing the quarter marker, continued to gain ground at mid-stretch, finished evenly in the final furlong, could not reel in PERFORMATIVE in the late stages and held safely at the end for second. NUESTRO ENGREIDO showed good early speed and set a fast pace while pressured into the turn, held a narrow advantage to the quarter marker while carving out quick fractions, stubbornly battled against PERFORMATIVE to mid-stretch, weakened in the final stages, was outfinished for second and just held for third. MEDAL ICE chased the fast pace from the inside, gained ground nearing the quarter marker, ran evenly to mid-stretch and flattened out in the final stages. DOGE OF VENICE was prominent in the early running and pressed the fast early pace while outside of NUESTRO ENGREIDO, lost position nearing the quarter marker, could not keep pace into upper stretch and gave way. DADDY'SDARLINGBOY chased the fast pace, raced outside of a rival to the quarter marker and lacked a response in the stretch drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Nuestro Engreido
ENTRY.COMMENT: showed speed,set pressured pace,fought back stretch,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Doge of Venice
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace,3wide,lost position turn,gave way stretch

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Jason Hall, Joe Wheeler and HerschelMartindale

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 99. Allowance Purse 27000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (Non-starters For Claiming Price $16,000 Or Less In The Last Three Starts Preferred)(Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won An Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs. Unless Entered For A Claiming Price).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANITANEWMERCEDES broke alertly and was sent to establish the early lead, set decent fractions while prompted through the backstretch run, was headed by SUPERMAZEL at the quarter marker, re-established the lead in upper stretch and took a narrow advantage to the furlong marker, gamely battled to deep stretch while inside of SUPERMAZEL and determinedly prevailed at the finish. SUPERMAZEL was forwardly placed into the first turn and stalked the pace into the backstretch run, prompted the decent fractions to the half-mile pole and drew to even terms with ANITANEWMERCEDES at the quarter marker, dueled with that rival to the furlong pole, made a steady gain in deep stretch, could not get by the determined winner in the final strides and bested the rest. ENOS SLAUGHTER settled off of the early pace, raced four wide along the first turn and maintained that four wide path through the backstretch run, gained ground while four wide along the far turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch while within aim, could not muster the needed late response and just held for third. SECRET CLUB tracked the decent fractions from a three wide path, made a steady gain through the backstretch run and came within aim nearing the quarter marker, could not sustain that bid in the stretch and weakened in the drive. SEA OF LIBERTY was allowed to settle, saved ground through the backstretch run while not far back, swung five wide for the drive and did not offer a late response.

ENTRY.NAME: Sea of Liberty
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside,not far back,swung 5wide stretch,no late response

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SACRAMENTO RACE 8 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 98. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since May 15 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming, An d Starter Races For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIL MIRACLE MAN broke best and was content to cede the early lead to IL CAPITANO then tracked well behind to the half mile marker, launched a bid with three furlongs to go, collared the pacesetter in the stretch and held sway under firm handling. IL CAPITANO broke a step slow then hustled to bid for the lead going into the first turn, took command passing the seven-eighths pole and went unchallenged on the lead, widened while under a snug hold down the backstretch, responded under pressure when confronted by the eventual winner at the top of the stretch, was unable to match strides late but finished well enough to hold the place. LOOKIN FOR REVENGE allowed to settle early, held position down the backstretch but well behind the early leader, began a rally from the three furlong pole and ran on somewhat one paced but good enough to hold third. LORD WIMBORNE (IRE) devoid of any speed in the early going, started a run from the far turn that carried wide into the stretch and ran on well down the middle of the track and came up just short of a minor award. POUR ON THE COLE tracked to the outside LOOKIN FOR REVENGE down the backstretch, came under pressure on the far turn and was outrun from there.

ENTRY.NAME: Lookin for Revenge
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, rallied from 3/8, one-paced, held 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Pour On the Cole
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked from well back in 2p, under pressure far turn, outrun

ENTRY.NAME: Lord Wimborne (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: outrun to far turn, bid 3/8 wide rally stretch, came up short

ENTRY.NAME: Lil Miracle Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked runaway pacesetter, bid 3/8, took command, held

ENTRY.NAME: Il Capitano
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, took command 1st turn, big lead to stretch, held 2nd
